Audio is synced and the quality is as good as a Telesync (camera set up in the cinema camera booth with tripod with audio directly connected to the source) will ever get (Telecine implies that a special camera was used or that the physical film was scanned frame by frame which is highly unlikely).

If 1080p is a 10, 720p is a 9, DVD is a 8, purchased VHS is 7, copied purchased VHS is 6, VHS recorded from TV is a 5, third copy made of that recording is a 4, a good cam is a 3, unfocused and cropped cam is a 2 and 1 being unwatchable I'd give this release:

V: 5
A: 6

In other words until there's a DVD or Blu-Ray release (screener or otherwise) this is probably the best quality you will get. Thanks for a good release, me and my GF both enjoyed the movie :)

If you want to really enjoy this movie, then please do not download this dirty print. Don't waste bandwidth. Wait for the BRrip 720p. The Blue ray will release on 29  March 2011.
